p:
This paper will argue that the key elements of cropping system adaptation to climate change are:
 
  
   (i)

Access to elite germplasm from other regions that currently experience conditions likely to occur in the target region as a result of climate change;
  
  
   (ii)

Rapid breeding cycles that provide farmers with a steady stream of new cultivars developed in and for the current climate;
  
  
   (iii)

Evaluation of potential new cultivars under the full range of climate conditions they are likely to encounter over their commercial life;
  
  
   (iv)

Seed systems that deliver new varieties to farmers quickly, and then just as quickly replace them, keeping pace with the changing climate.
